The paper proposes a novel mining method for predicting or diagnosing cancers using a dataset of TP53 gene mutations. This involves selecting a minimum number of fields in training and testing a quick propagation algorithm. This paper involves machine learning (ML) techniques, specifically neural networks, and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
